<h2>Emulator</h2>
<p>
    The Emulator API Call takes the same POST Body as the Assembler API Call, but instead of returning a list of strings it returns a list
    of Frames.  These Frames represent each TState for each instruction. For the SAP1, every instruction will have 6 TStates.  It is
    good to note that if there is an emulation error, it will return different status code. Make sure to check out the 
    <a href="/swagger/" target="_blank">Swagger Page</a> for more information.
    <br />
    <br />
    In order to parse correctly, the <code>requestBody</code> JSON must be escaped properly when assigning it directly to a string.
    If you are using <code>System.Text.Json</code> to create the <code>requestBody</code>, this will be handled automatically.
</p>
